Excellent—your C++ code is now running. The remaining problem is **missing Qt Quick Controls runtime packages**.

The key error is:

```text
module "QtQuick.Templates" plugin "qtquicktemplates2plugin" not found
```

This is **not** a MAVSDK or PX4 issue.

## Install the missing Qt packages

Run:

```bash
sudo apt update

sudo apt install \
qml6-module-qtquick-controls \
qml6-module-qtquick-templates \
qml6-module-qtquick-layouts \
qml6-module-qtquick-window \
qml6-module-qtqml \
qml6-module-qtquick
```

If one of those package names doesn't exist, run:

```bash
apt-cache search qml6-module-qtquick
```

and paste the output.

---

## Check that the plugin is installed

Run:

```bash
find /usr -name qtquicktemplates2plugin\*
```

You should find something like:

```text
/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/qt6/qml/QtQuick/Templates/qtquicktemplates2plugin.so
```

---

## Quick workaround

If you don't want to install Qt Quick Controls yet, replace your `Main.qml` with this minimal QML that uses only `QtQuick`:

```qml
import QtQuick 2.15

Rectangle {
    width: 600
    height: 400
    color: "white"

    Text {
        anchors.centerIn: parent
        text: drone.connected ? "Connected" : "Waiting for PX4..."
        font.pixelSize: 28
    }
}
```

This avoids `ApplicationWindow` and `QtQuick.Controls` entirely and should let you verify the rest of the application.

